text.tspan: General
The Scralaxy Team 2021-2023
- I have added back content and changes made from 0.0.4 to 0.1.1.5 that were removed.
- Using and modifying a Turbo Mode detection system created by David_Nowak123, the
game now requires you to be using Turbo Mode. If you aren't, you'll be greeted with a
screen telling you to enable it. If you are, you'll be directed to the title screen.
- Added placeholder buttons to some menus, so they at least feel somewhat alive even
though there's nothing there yet. Feel free to add, remove, or reposition buttons.
Including Characters, Stages, e.t.c.
Graphical
New Features
Bug Fixes
With Characters from Nintendo Co., Ltd.
v
S C R U L T I M A T E
- The UI system has been modified in multiple ways, so I introduce SUI2 or Scrultimate
User Interface 2.0! It is built upon the previous UI system which will now be dubbed SUI.
I have added a bunch of comments detailing each part of the system in the SUI2 sprite.
Let's hope Scratch doesn't make them disappear like they did when I was writing them!
- I have attempted to make things such as the presents animation and changelog look
better when ran in Turbo Mode. Unfortunately I could not fix the "PRESS SPACE" text so it
currently just stays there. If anyone can fix this that'd be pretty nice, but it's not important.
- Also I have modified some buttons like settings and the smash
in the smash menu but I don't have much space left here!!!
-VARIOUS OTHER GRAPHICS MODIFIED!!!
- Honestly I think I broke more stuff instead of fixing things. I'm gonna give myself some
credit though, I managed to fix some big problems all by myself! Like menu navigation
was broken, getting into the game was broken, various things were just... Broken... But
not anymore! There are still some issues though...
- There is currently a major issue where inputs aren't working in game. However, by going
into the "IS" sprite and clicking on the two "Define" scripts, it should enable the inputs
once more. I have no idea why this issue occured. It will be fixed.
- For devs who use Unspecified Addon, some sprites have been grouped into folders! I
hope this helps with navigation.
